  <h2>The Future: What's Coming Next</h2>
  
  <p>
    AI in travel is evolving rapidly. Emerging trends to watch:
  </p>
  
  <h3>Hyper-Personalization</h3>
  <p>
    AI will create truly personalized itineraries—not just destination recommendations, 
    but specific activities, restaurants, and timing based on individual preferences.
  </p>

  <h3>Predictive Service</h3>
  <p>
    AI will anticipate problems before they occur. Flight likely to be delayed? 
    Automatically notify the customer and suggest alternatives. Weather forecast 
    looks bad for an outdoor activity? Proactively offer rebooking options.
  </p>

  <h3>Voice and Multimodal Interfaces</h3>
  <p>
    Beyond text chatbots, AI will enable voice-based booking and planning through 
    smart speakers and phone assistants.
  </p>

  <h3>Autonomous Operations</h3>
  <p>
    Routine operational tasks—supplier confirmations, document verification, payment 
    reconciliation—will be handled entirely by AI, with humans only involved for 
    exceptions.
  </p>
  
  <p>
    The travel businesses that embrace AI thoughtfully—focusing on real problems, 
    maintaining human connection, and continuously learning—will thrive in this 
    new era. Those that resist will find themselves increasingly unable to compete 
    on speed, cost, or customer experience.
